gomodel:SYNGO_2509  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"Electron micrographs showing immunoperoxidase labeling for the D2 receptor within dendrites (D2-d in panel a and c), spines (D2-s in panel b), and axon terminals (D2-t in panels d and e) within the ICMs (panels a and d) and BLA (panels b, c, and e) of the AMG\"\n- \"The D2R was frequently observed within dendrites (Fig. 6a, c) and spines (Fig. 6b).\"\n- \"The D2R was frequently found within axonal profiles (Fig. 6d, e). Some of these formed either symmetric or asymmetric synapses (Fig. 6e) onto spines or distal dendrites.\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Eleven adult male Spraque Dawley rats weighing 300-400 g were used in this study.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2509" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

